Title: Yangians and Gelfand-Zetlin bases
Author: M. Nazarov and Vitaly Tarasov
Comments: 14 pages
Report-no: RIMS-913
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Quantum Algebra
Journal-ref: Publ.Res.Inst.Math.Sci.Kyoto 30 (1994) 459-478
\\
  We establish a relationship between the modern theory of Yangians and the
classical construction of the Gelfand-Zetlin bases for the complex Lie algebra
$\gn$. Our approach allows us to produce the $q$-analogues of the
Gelfand-Zetlin formulae in a straightforward way.
